<li id="cite_note-Brehm1981-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Brehm1981_1-0" title="">^</a></b> Brehm, S. S., &amp; Brehm, J. W. (1981). <i>Psychological Reactance: A Theory of Freedom and Control</i>. Academic Press.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Silvia2005-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Silvia2005_2-0" title="">^</a></b> Silvia, P. J. (2005). Deflecting reactance: The role of similarity in increasing compliance and reducing resistance. <i>Basic and Applied Social Psychology, 27,</i> 277–284.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Miller2006-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Miller2006_3-0" title="">^</a></b> *Miller, C. H., Burgoon, M., Grandpre, J., &amp; Alvaro, E. (2006). Identifying principal risk factors for the initiation of adolescent smoking behaviors: The significance of psychological reactance. <i>Health Communication 19,</i> 241-252.</li>
<li id="cite_note-DillardShen2005-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-DillardShen2005_4-0" title="">^</a></b> Dillard, J., &amp; Shen, L. (2005). On the nature of reactance and its role in persuasive health communication. <i>Communication Monographs,</i> 72, 144-168.</li>
